  <h3>Engines is for running servers</h3>

  <p>Individuals can use Engine for hosting a blog, holding a media library, instant messaging, social networking, and multiplayer gaming.</p>

  <p>Commercial users can run software for online stores, managing projects, CRM, fleet tracking, voip, accounting, document sharing, group contacts/calendar, and even ERP.</p>

  <p>Schools can host an education platform server, email and more.</p>

  <p>There is an almost limitless range of software applications that can run on Engines.</p>
  
  <h3>Easy to use</h3>

  <p>Engines provides you with an easy-to-use interface to control your server and its software.</p>

  <p>Software applications are quick and straightforward to install, configure and maintain. The installation process is similar to the app store experience that you know from using your phone and tablet.</p>

  <h3>Flexible</h3>

  <p>Run Engines on a computer at home or in the office, or on a virtual machine hosted in the cloud.

  <p>Engines runs multiple applications on the one machine. Each application is self-contained and executed separately for stability and security.</p>

  <p>Files and data can be readily shared between Engines, and back-ups are simple to set-up and run.</p>

